results with a different move order, but this is the cleanest one. He is
attacking the queen and, immediately, driving the knight to c4. Next, he will
play Nd2 and Nb3, and will double the rooks on the a-line.} (17. Rd1 $5) (17.
Nbd2 $5) (17. Qxd7+ $6 Nxd7 {Stoping Ne5 and helping Black develop his pieces
better.}) (17. Qa5 $6 {There is no need to keep the queens on the board. It's
not easy to press the a5 with the queen in front of the rook.}) 17... Qxa4 18.
