pawn; so the rooks cannot attack it. Similarly, it's attacking the d6-bishop,
and Black should treat him.} Bc7 20. Nbd2 {The other knight is driving to b3
in order to increase the pressure against the a5. All of White's pieces have a
clear scope and initiative. Please notice that Black is behind the development.
} Ke7 21. Rea1 a5 22. Nb3 {The computer evaluates the position as equal, but
